Date:  0/0/1898
Source:  Austral English
Author:
Vol / Page:  254
Edition:
Quote:  <i>Kotukutuku, n</i>. Maori name for the New Zealand tree, <i>Fuchsia excorticata</i>, Linn., N.O. <i>Onagrarieae</i>; written also <i>Kohutuhutu</i>. This name is not much used, but is corrupted into <i>Tookytook</i> (q.v.). See <i>Konini</i> and <i>Fuchsia. </i>
Notes:

